{
  "stem": "25423.6",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Three, and because of my father's contact with the Metropolitan, who was my benefactor, and his brother.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And finally, because of resiliency. to submerge in monastic life with an Eastern monastic community is not an easy job.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "About what?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, no, no.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Having fought in the Polish army and having spent three years in combat in Israel, I'm not pestered by these things at all.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I see the [INAUDIBLE] was there, mitzvah tanks run aground, I find it very amusing, you see, and entertaining.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When I see women rabbis in the synagogue, which I occasionally might visit, I see trampling on tradition, which cause me a lot of harm, because I was chased in those days because I'm a Jew.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So seeing people trample-- trampling on their own traditions makes me angry.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But otherwise, I am a neutral observer, as I have won-- I have fought my battles.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I won some.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I lost some, as everybody else.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't find my story unique or special.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's unique in only one point, that I was fortunate not to be in the clutches of the Germans for too long.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So I was not exposed to this horror of dehumanization, as my friend Father Petras who, because of his assistance to the Metropolitan and variety of activities which were anti-Nazi, ended in Dachau.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh, you speak about the book?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I got a phone call from the Shoah Institute, and a charming young lady, Victoria, who inquired whether I would like to testify.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My answer was yes, because I wish to take every opportunity to create a record and a memory of those people who perished.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] sitting here, I speak, essentially, for a community which was wiped out.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
